   : sudo need to be set up for at least the user running this script.
     This command should give userX basic sudo capabilities:
        On Debian / Ubuntu          --> usermod -a -G sudo userX
        On CentOS / Redhat / Gentoo --> usermod -a -G wheel userX
   : ninja (only when using the -n option)
 -------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 General
   : Many script, git and build options can be set or changed.
     Current settings are:

     - Script related
